    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-02T15:49:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-02T15:49:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/615.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-02T16:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1911—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President embarked this afternoon on the Haitian war vessel formerly the <hi
                        rend="italic">American</hi> and will await arrival of the merchant vessel on
                    Friday. The city is in charge of a committee of public safety composed of
                    prominent men, who have guaranteed the safety of life and property.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
